{"article_id":"WdyfH5zsIw1FrBQC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"US President Donald Trump has renewed a threat","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"to declare a national emergency","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"to fund the construction of a wall on the Mexican border .","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"A row with Democrats","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"over funding the wall","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"has left the government partially shut down for 20 days ,","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"leaving some 800,000 federal employees unpaid .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"On Saturday , the shutdown becomes the longest in US history .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Mr Trump says","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"the wall , a key campaign pledge , is needed","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"to tackle a security crisis of illegal immigration .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"The Democrats say","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"the wall is an `` immorality '' and a waste of taxpayers ' money .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"President Trump has refused to sign legislation","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"to fund and reopen the government","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"if it does not include $ 5.7bn","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"( £4.5bn )","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"for the wall .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"He issued the threat on a visit on Thursday to a border patrol station in McAllen , in the Rio Grande Valley of Texas .","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"He said","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"if Congress did not approve funding for the wall ,","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"he would `` probably ...","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"I would almost say","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"definitely '' declare a national emergency","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"to bypass lawmakers .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"`` I have the absolute right","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"to declare a national emergency , ''","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"In a later interview with Fox News , he doubled down ,","depth":5},{"id":30,"text":"declaring :","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"`` If we do n't make a deal with Congress ,","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"most likely I will do that .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"`` I would actually say","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"I would .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"I ca n't imagine any reason","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"why not ,","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"because I 'm allowed to do it . '' `` The law is 100 percent on my side , ''","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"Mr Trump would have the right","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"to undertake such a construction project in times of war and national emergency ,","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"usually allocating funds from the department of defence .","depth":5},{"id":42,"text":"But bypassing Congress would be hugely controversial ,","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"sparking allegations of the overuse of executive powers","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"and it would almost certainly face huge legal challenges .","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"Some US media reports suggest","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"the White House is considering diverting some of the $ 13.9bn","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"( £10.9bn )","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"allocated last year by Congress for disaster relief in such areas as Puerto Rico , Texas and California","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"to pay for the wall .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"NBC News reported on Thursday","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"that Mr Trump had been briefed on such a plan","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"but the White House denied it .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Analysts say","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"the national emergency move would provide political cover","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"to reopen government","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"while allowing Mr Trump to argue","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"he has done all","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"he can","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"to fulfil his campaign promise .","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"The BBC 's David Willis in Washington says","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"that ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"with no further talks with the Democrats planned ,","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"this now seems the most likely option for the president .","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"Republican Senator Lindsey Graham , a key Trump ally , said","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"there was no other pathway forward .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"He was speaking at McAllen station , behind a display of weapons and cash","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"said to have been seized by the border patrol .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"He was joined by border patrol agents , and relatives of people","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"killed by illegal immigrants .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"`` If we do n't have a barrier ...","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"you 're not going to be able to solve this problem , ''","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"adding","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"that people faced `` hard work '' , `` gruelling problems '' and `` a lot of death ''","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"without it .","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"Mr Trump added :","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"`` They say a wall is medieval ...","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"There are some things","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"that work . ''","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"The president said in a national address on Tuesday","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"the wall was needed","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"to stem a `` growing humanitarian and security crisis at our southern border '' ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"involving `` thousands of illegal immigrants '' .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"He pointed to illegal drug supplies , people trafficking and criminal acts by illegal immigrants in the US .","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"The Democrats say","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"the wall is `` ineffective '' and `` unnecessary '' and an expensive bill to taxpayers","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"the president had said","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"Mexico would foot .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"Speaking on Thursday ,","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"Mr Trump said","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"he never meant","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"that Mexico would make a one-time payment for the wall .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"`` When I said","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"Mexico would pay for the wall in front of thousands and thousands of people ...","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"obviously I never meant","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"Mexico would write a cheque , ''","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"However , this is contradicted by an archived campaign memo from 2016 ,","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"where Mr Trump outlined","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"how he planned to `` compel Mexico to make a one-time payment '' of $ 5-10bn","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"( £4bn-£8bn )","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"for the wall .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"Mr Trump said on Thursday","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"that ,","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"instead of a direct payment , Mexico would be `` paying for the wall indirectly , many , many times over '' , under a new trade deal between the US , Mexico and Canada .","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"Economists have disputed this","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"and critics say","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"that any savings","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"incurred due to the deal","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"would go directly to private businesses","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"rather than flow into US Treasury .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"Partial shutdowns occur","depth":3},{"id":114,"text":"when Congress can not agree a budget by a certain deadline","depth":4},{"id":115,"text":"or the president refuses to sign it .","depth":4},{"id":116,"text":"This shutdown ,","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"which began on 22 December ,","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"has closed 25 % of the government .","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"Of the 800,000 federal employees affected , about 350,000 are furloughed","depth":7},{"id":120,"text":"- a kind of temporary lay off -","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"and the rest are working","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"without pay .","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"The first pay day since the shutdown falls on Friday and will pass","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"without workers getting salaries .","depth":6},{"id":125,"text":"They include prison guards , airport security screening staff , and members of the FBI .","depth":5},{"id":126,"text":"Some affected federal workers","depth":6},{"id":127,"text":"who spoke to the BBC","depth":6},{"id":128,"text":"said","depth":5},{"id":129,"text":"they had resorted to a number of measures ,","depth":5},{"id":130,"text":"including taking other jobs ,","depth":6},{"id":131,"text":"racking up credit card bills ,","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"tapping into savings","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"or taking on loans at high interest rates","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"to pay their bills .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":269,"left":247,"right":268,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":247,"left":173,"right":246,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":153,"right":172,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":147,"right":152,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":142,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":137,"right":141,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":0,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":136,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":140,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":139,"right":6,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":139,"left":138,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":138,"